 Following the President’s announcement of a nationwide lockdown, leading Port Elizabeth-based legal firm, Goldberg & de Villiers Inc on Tuesday announced that it has implemented measures to help curb the spread of the Coronavirus (Covid-19). Please take note of the following operational arrangements: "As a responsible business, we are taking every precaution to ensure the safety of our employees and our clients. We remain focused on giving our clients the attention they need and will respond to instructions and queries as quickly as possible," the firm said. "However, these are not normal times and we hope you will understand that there may be some delays that cannot be avoided. "Where possible we have  put  measures in place to minimise disruptions and to ensure that our business continues to run smoothly in order that we are in a position to provide you with the peace of mind you deserve. "Thank you for your support and be assured of our continuous service to you. "We wish you and your families good health during these testing times." Litigation Department Herman Bekker  061 239 3006  herman@goldlaw.co.za Kugen Pillay  060 997 7011  kugen@goldlaw.co.za Estates Department Bardine Hall   082 536 8117   bardine@goldlaw.co.za Commercial and Corporate Law Department Sandy Scholtz  082 760 7591 sandy@goldlaw.co.za Recoveries Department Sandy Scholtz   082 760 7591 sandy@goldlaw.co.za Conveyancing and Property Law Department Adri Ludorf   082 657 0362  adri@goldlaw.co.za Tracey Watson-Gill     084 812 3234 twg@goldlaw.co.za Labour and Human Resources Department Tracey Mouton 082 898 7841  traceym@goldlaw.co.za Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visi